node.text: As of October 2020, about 164,000 small businesses have closed and 60% will never reopen. This year, more than ever, shopping small MATTERS. A SPECIAL new episode of Home Town all about local love for Laurel and Wetumpka airs tonight at 8/7 c! Y’all don’t miss it!#SmallTogether

node.title: Without small businesses, towns like Laurel die.

node.text: I’ve not picked up my guitar in so long, but Helen loves this one and it would do y’all good to know it too. I’m rusty, forgetting chords, but it still feels good to sing a song.

node.title: Something to Love (cover) by @jasonisbell and the 400 unit

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Erin Napier on July 19, 2021 tagging @scotsman.co. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: This is not a beautiful, styled and staged photo of what I cooked for dinner but it is the first real meal I have cooked since Mae was born. Ben’s favorite pork tenderloin with roasted vegetables and basil rice. Our baby is 7 weeks old now, and it took us this long to figure out how to plan and juggle and cook a real meal with two small children under foot or in my arms. since Ben was home early it wasn’t even chaotic, and there was time for 2 (!!!) bedtime books for Helen. I am impressed and amazed by the wherewithal of moms with more than two kids, and I’m very proud we have made this baby (😉) step toward normal days. Onward, moms and dads!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Erin Napier on July 18, 2021 tagging @scotsman.co. May be an image of 1 person, screen, television and indoor.

node.text: We’ve waited before taking Helen to see her first movie in the theater because we wanted to wait for the right one. A magical one. She’s seen this a dozen times at home and decided a long time ago that Elliott will be her husband when she grows up. When the orchestra plays the score at the end it will make you cry when you see it on the big screen. For Elliott, it’s saying goodbye to ET, for me, it was one more milestone in her tiny life.

node.text: @scotsman.co’s first day back on #BensWorkshop with @sullivangrams was my first solo midnight feeding and day with 2 little ones and I’m pretty proud of how we all survived it. I am so incredibly proud of Big and the team that makes his show. I wish you could see how hard they work to bring it to life. (photos by @brookedavisjefcoat)

node.text: To the king of dad jokes, the biggest man with a heart of gold, who makes his girls feel like the most special ones on the earth: thank you for making us laugh. We love you @scotsman.co! (nice cameo here, @randy.sherrell)
